        "disaster_description": "With the intensification of the southwest monsoon, Sri Lanka has experienced heavy rainfall in the Western, Sabaragamuwa, and Southern provinces. This unusual expansion of the southwest monsoon began early in October 2023, with severe rainy conditions starting on 6 October 2023. A red warning was issued to 7 districts on 7 October 2023. The Disaster Management Centre reported on October 9, 2023, that many people were displaced due to floods and landslides in the Gampaha, Matara, and Galle districts. The adverse weather conditions caused seven deaths and affected more than 75,000 people in 13 districts. Subsequent heavy rainfall and strong winds in November and December 2023, and January 2024, led to further floods, landslides, and severe weather-related incidents, resulting in additional casualties and damage across the country.",
