        "disaster_description": "On 16 September 2022, the Ethiopia Ministry of Health declared a cholera outbreak in the Harana Buluk and Berbere woredas of Bale Zone, Oromia Region. The outbreak has spread to multiple regions, including Somali, SNNP, and Sidama, affecting numerous woredas and resulting in thousands of cases and hundreds of deaths. The outbreak is attributed to the use of unsafe water from contaminated sources, limited access to water and sanitation services, and poor hygiene practices. The outbreak has been ongoing since 27 August 2022, with significant challenges in controlling its spread due to insufficient funding, limited partner presence, and low water supply coverage.",
