    "https://reliefweb.int/disaster/ep-2019-000184-bgd": {
        "disaster_title": "Bangladesh: Measles Outbreak - Sep 2019",
        "disaster_type": ["Epidemic"],
        "date": "2019-09",
        "disaster_description": "Refugee camps in Bangladesh have seen a sustained high number of measles cases from September through November 2019. More than 1,510 measles cases have been reported for 2019, with over 110 of these manifesting only in the last week. In December, instances of measles have risen. During the first week of the month, another 125 suspected measles cases reported to the WHO. As of 22 December, there were 2,175 measles cases reported during 2019. The number of suspected cases reported during Week 51 was 157. A Measles Outbreak Response Immunization is scheduled to occur from 12 January to 12 February, 2020. The immunization will target an age group ranging from six months old to less than 10 years old in the camp population. As of 29 December, there were 210 suspected measles cases were reported during week 52. This brings the total measles cases during 2019 to 2,446 with 0.1% morbidity. During the first week of 2020, there were 264 measles cases reported with 0.7 per cent morbidity. The number of measles cases has remained high since September 2019. More than 370 suspected measles cases were reported between 13 and 19 of January. This brings the total of measles cases reported in 2020 to almost 1,100. The instances of reported measles cases has continued to rise through the month. About 254 suspected measles cases were reported between 20 and 26 of January. This brought the total of measles cases reported in 2020 to over 1,500. As of 9 February, there were 2,662 measles cases reported in 2020. The ongoing measles outbreak response Immunization in the camps expected to be completed by February 12. The Measles Outbreak Response Immunization was completed in the camps. Total 292,394 doses were administered in children 6 month to <10 years. In the last three weeks, number of cases showed a decreasing trend with total of 111 suspected measles cases reported during week 8 of 2020. As of 23 February, there were 3,320 cases report in 2020. During week 11 of 2020, a total of 36 suspected measles cases were reported, bringing the total number of cases reported in 2020 to 4,188. This is the fifth week that the number of cases showed a decreasing trend.",
        "interventions": "A Measles Outbreak Response Immunization was conducted from 12 January to 12 February, 2020, targeting children aged six months to less than 10 years in the camp population. A total of 292,394 doses were administered.",
