    "https://reliefweb.int/disaster/fl-2021-000209-mys": {
        "disaster_title": "Malaysia: Flash Floods - Dec 2021",
        "disaster_type": ["Flash Floods", "Landslides"],
        "date": "16 December 2021",
        "disaster_description": "The newly formed Tropical Depression TWENTYNINE made landfall in an area in Kemaman District (southern Terengganu State, north-eastern Peninsular Malaysia) in the late evening of 16 December. More than 380 people have been displaced to evacuation centres in Terengganu and Kelantan States. At least two people died (one in Pahang and another in Terengganu States). The Malaysian National Disaster Command Centre (NDCC) reports 37,670 people displaced in 388 evacuations centres across eight States. Floodwaters have damaged buildings, roads, and infrastructure, including three water treatment plants in Selangor. Around 70,000 people are directly impacted, with 67,629 persons displaced in 470 evacuation centres. As of 23 December, 37 deaths have been reported. The flooding significantly impacted people's livelihoods, especially in Selangor and Kuala Lumpur. Economic losses are estimated at around USD 200 million. There have been unscheduled water cuts and disruptions to the electricity supply. Search and rescue efforts have been hampered by a lack of assets and coordination issues. Medical evacuations were necessary as the elderly and people with chronic diseases suffered from lack of food, running water, disrupted electricity supply, and shortage of medication. Since mid-December, floods and landslides caused by heavy rainfall have been affecting Malaysia, with up to 50 people dead and two missing. As of 3 January, the Malaysia National Disaster Management Agency (NADMA) confirms that several states are still affected by floods.",
        "interventions": "Evacuation of more than 380 people to centres in Terengganu and Kelantan States. The Malaysian National Disaster Command Centre (NDCC) and Malaysia’s Agensi Pengurusan Bencana (NADMA) have been involved in managing the disaster. Search and rescue operations have been conducted, although hampered by a lack of assets and coordination issues. Medical evacuations were carried out for the elderly and people with chronic diseases.",
        "affected_countries": ["Malaysia"],
        "sources": ["AHA Centre", "ECHO", "Malaysian National Disaster Command Centre (NDCC)", "Malaysia’s Agensi Pengurusan Bencana (NADMA)", "IFRC", "ASEAN Disaster Information Network (ADINet)"],
        "language": "English"
    }
}

https://reliefweb.int/disaster/fl-2020-0:
