        "disaster_description": "In June 2016, severe weather, including heavy rain, thunderstorms and hail, affected the central and southern areas of China, causing casualties and damage. Five people died, one went missing, 11 were injured, over 3,600 people were evacuated, and over 23,600 houses were partially or fully damaged in several provinces. By 23 June, 9 million people were affected by torrential rainfall across 10 provinces, with severe weather causing 98 deaths and at least 800 injuries. Torrential rainfall over the Yangtze River exacerbated flooding, affecting nearly 2.8 million people in 11 provinces. Heavy rains and hailstorms triggered severe floods and landslides, affecting over 600,000 people and displacing over 240,000. Continuous heavy rainfall from 18 July led to 417 flood-related deaths. In August, flooding affected around 78,000 people in five provinces. Typhoons Meranti and Malakas affected 2.7 million people in September, and Typhoon Megi made landfall in late September.",
