        "disaster_description": "Heavy rainfall over a period of several days in Attapeu Province resulted in dangerously high river and dam levels. An incident at the Xepien-Xenamnoy Hydropower dam construction in Attapeu province resulted in flash flooding, with eight villages affected. The collapse of the dam affected nearly 7,000 people and displaced more than 1,000 people. More than 100 houses were damaged, forcing people to seek shelter in local government buildings and schools. Tropical Storm Son-Tinh affected several provinces, the most severe being Sanamxay District in the Attapeu Province. This is the largest flood the country has seen in the past 10 years. Flood waters caused by the break of Xepien-Xenamnoyu dam in southern Lao PDR are flowing downstream, resulting in the evacuation of more than 5,600 people in Stung Treng Province, northern Cambodia. Tropical Cyclone Bebinca led to flooding in northern Laos, with impacts also felt in the south of the country.",
        "interventions": "Red Cross teams in the Attepeu branch distributed clothing, food, and drinking water to households in the affected area. The IFRC released an appeal seeking 2.9 million Swiss francs to support the Lao Red Cross to deliver assistance to 7,500 people for 18 months. The UN activated five clusters: WASH, Health, Food Security and Nutrition, Shelter, and Logistics. Local authorities and NGOs distributed relief items and deployed staff to assist in monitoring the situation. The Humanitarian Country Team launched a Disaster Response Plan to provide life-saving assistance to 13,100 people affected by the flash floods. UNICEF and partners, with support from USAID, installed water points and toilets in the camps, and distributed 200,000 water purification tablets. A new six-month programme was launched with US$ 3.5 million from the Central Emergency Response Fund to provide humanitarian assistance to 110,000 households in the six most affected districts of Khammouane province.",
        "affected_countries": ["Cambodia", "Lao People's Democratic Republic (the)"],
        "sources": ["UNCT Laos/OCHA", "IFRC/Lao Red Cross", "OCHA", "UNICEF"],
        "language": "English"
