        "interventions": "Ebola vaccination of people at high risk began in Guinea as the emergency response was escalated to counter the spread of the virus. As of 3 March, 17 cumulative cases were declared, with eight deaths. By 6 April, 23 cases were notified, including 16 confirmed and 7 probable cases, with 12 deaths recorded. 5,125 people were vaccinated. By 13 May, 9,829 people were inoculated, including 2,694 frontline staff. UNICEF provided psychosocial support to 132 children in the families of contact cases. By 1 June, 10,873 people were inoculated. The outbreak was declared over on 19 June 2021.",
