        "disaster_description": "Torrential monsoon rains and rising river levels have caused flooding. In Kachin State, more than 6,200 people have been evacuated to 39 sites in Myitkyina, Bhamo and Shwegu townships as of 13 July. Rakhine, Chin and Mon states are also being hit by floods. Heavy rainfall during Myanmar’s monsoon season resulted in the Laymyo River overflowing at the beginning of July. By 14 July, all of the more than 3,400 people living in the IDP camp of Sin Baw Kaing village, Mrauk-U Township, were affected, and had to be relocated. Monsoon rains and overflowing rivers have triggered seasonal floods in eight states and regions, with evacuations in many locations. A landslide, caused by the heavy rainfall, occurred in Paung Township, Mon State, resulting in casualties and missing persons. More than 231,000 people have been affected in various states and regions.",
